  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): from main branch\r\n* OS: macOS\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): 3.9\r\n \r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nCurrently, `titanaboa` uses vyper as a dependency.\r\nAnd vyper has a strict pin on `semantic-version` lib.\r\nThis causes conflicts with other packages in the ecosystem, such as `py-tokenlists`, which is used by the `ape-tokens` plugin which is one of the `recommended-plugins` from Ape.\r\n\r\nResolving this will improve compatibility between the Ape framework and Titanaboa.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\n* Upgrade semantic-version\r\n* OR find a way to support broader range (copy in methods or components of the library?)\r\n",
